35// This function is only expected to be called on the signaling thread.
36// On the other hand, some test or even production setups may use
37// several signaling threads.
38int GenerateUniqueId() {
39 static std::atomic<int> g_unique_id{0};
40
41 return ++g_unique_id;
42}
43
44// Returns true if a "per-sender" encoding parameter contains a value that isn't
45// its default. Currently max_bitrate_bps and bitrate_priority both are
46// implemented "per-sender," meaning that these encoding parameters
47// are used for the RtpSender as a whole, not for a specific encoding layer.
48// This is done by setting these encoding parameters at index 0 of
49// RtpParameters.encodings. This function can be used to check if these
50// parameters are set at any index other than 0 of RtpParameters.encodings,
51// because they are currently unimplemented to be used for a specific encoding
52// layer.
53bool PerSenderRtpEncodingParameterHasValue(
54 const RtpEncodingParameters& encoding_params) {
55 if (encoding_params.bitrate_priority != kDefaultBitratePriority ||
56 encoding_params.network_priority != Priority::kLow) {
57 return true;
58 }
59 return false;
60}
61
62void RemoveEncodingLayers(const std::vector<std::string>& rids,
63 std::vector<RtpEncodingParameters>* encodings) {
64 RTC_DCHECK(encodings);
65 encodings->erase(
66 std::remove_if(encodings->begin(), encodings->end(),
67 [&rids](const RtpEncodingParameters& encoding) {
68 return absl::c_linear_search(rids, encoding.rid);
69 }),
70 encodings->end());
71}
72
73RtpParameters RestoreEncodingLayers(
74 const RtpParameters& parameters,
75 const std::vector<std::string>& removed_rids,
76 const std::vector<RtpEncodingParameters>& all_layers) {
77 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(parameters.encodings.size() + removed_rids.size(),
78 all_layers.size());
79 RtpParameters result(parameters);
80 result.encodings.clear();
81 size_t index = 0;
82 for (const RtpEncodingParameters& encoding : all_layers) {
83 if (absl::c_linear_search(removed_rids, encoding.rid)) {
84 result.encodings.push_back(encoding);
85 continue;
86 }
87 result.encodings.push_back(parameters.encodings[index++]);
88 }
89 return result;
90}

94// Returns true if any RtpParameters member that isn't implemented contains a
95// value.
96bool UnimplementedRtpParameterHasValue(const RtpParameters& parameters) {
97 if (!parameters.mid.empty()) {
98 return true;
99 }
100 for (size_t i = 0; i < parameters.encodings.size(); ++i) {
101 // Encoding parameters that are per-sender should only contain value at
102 // index 0.
103 if (i != 0 &&
104 PerSenderRtpEncodingParameterHasValue(parameters.encodings[i])) {
105 return true;
106 }
107 }
108 return false;
109}

138RtpParameters RtpSenderBase::GetParametersInternal() const {
139 if (stopped_) {
140 return RtpParameters();
141 }
142 if (!media_channel_ || !ssrc_) {
143 return init_parameters_;
144 }
145 return worker_thread_->Invoke<RtpParameters>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&] {
146 RtpParameters result = media_channel_->GetRtpSendParameters(ssrc_);
147 RemoveEncodingLayers(disabled_rids_, &result.encodings);
148 return result;
149 });
150}
151
152RtpParameters RtpSenderBase::GetParameters() const {
153 RtpParameters result = GetParametersInternal();
154 last_transaction_id_ = rtc::CreateRandomUuid();
155 result.transaction_id = last_transaction_id_.value();
156 return result;
157}
158
159RTCError RtpSenderBase::SetParametersInternal(const RtpParameters& parameters) {
160 RTC_DCHECK(!stopped_);
161
162 if (UnimplementedRtpParameterHasValue(parameters)) {
163 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(
164 RTCErrorType::UNSUPPORTED_PARAMETER,
165 "Attempted to set an unimplemented parameter of RtpParameters.");
166 }
167 if (!media_channel_ || !ssrc_) {
168 auto result = cricket::CheckRtpParametersInvalidModificationAndValues(
169 init_parameters_, parameters);
170 if (result.ok()) {
171 init_parameters_ = parameters;
172 }
173 return result;
174 }
175 return worker_thread_->Invoke<RTCError>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&] {
176 RtpParameters rtp_parameters = parameters;
177 if (!disabled_rids_.empty()) {
178 // Need to add the inactive layers.
179 RtpParameters old_parameters =
180 media_channel_->GetRtpSendParameters(ssrc_);
181 rtp_parameters = RestoreEncodingLayers(parameters, disabled_rids_,
182 old_parameters.encodings);
183 }
184 return media_channel_->SetRtpSendParameters(ssrc_, rtp_parameters);
185 });
186}
187
188RTCError RtpSenderBase::SetParameters(const RtpParameters& parameters) {
189 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "RtpSenderBase::SetParameters");
190 if (is_transceiver_stopped_) {
191 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(
192 RTCErrorType::INVALID_STATE,
193 "Cannot set parameters on sender of a stopped transceiver.");
194 }
195 if (stopped_) {
196 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_STATE,
197 "Cannot set parameters on a stopped sender.");
198 }
199 if (stopped_) {
200 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_STATE,
201 "Cannot set parameters on a stopped sender.");
202 }
203 if (!last_transaction_id_) {
204 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(
205 RTCErrorType::INVALID_STATE,
206 "Failed to set parameters since getParameters() has never been called"
207 " on this sender");
208 }
209 if (last_transaction_id_ != parameters.transaction_id) {
210 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(
211 RTCErrorType::INVALID_MODIFICATION,
212 "Failed to set parameters since the transaction_id doesn't match"
213 " the last value returned from getParameters()");
214 }
215
216 RTCError result = SetParametersInternal(parameters);
217 last_transaction_id_.reset();
218 return result;
219}

221void RtpSenderBase::SetStreams(const std::vector<std::string>& stream_ids) {
222 set_stream_ids(stream_ids);
223 if (set_streams_observer_)
224 set_streams_observer_->OnSetStreams();

227bool RtpSenderBase::SetTrack(MediaStreamTrackInterface* track) {
228 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "RtpSenderBase::SetTrack");
229 if (stopped_) {
230 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "SetTrack can't be called on a stopped RtpSender.";
231 return false;
232 }
233 if (track && track->kind() != track_kind()) {
234 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "SetTrack with " << track->kind()
235 << " called on RtpSender with " << track_kind()
236 << " track.";
237 return false;
238 }
239
240 // Detach from old track.
241 if (track_) {
242 DetachTrack();
243 track_->UnregisterObserver(this);
244 RemoveTrackFromStats();
245 }
246
247 // Attach to new track.
248 bool prev_can_send_track = can_send_track();
249 // Keep a reference to the old track to keep it alive until we call SetSend.
250 rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamTrackInterface> old_track = track_;
251 track_ = track;
252 if (track_) {
253 track_->RegisterObserver(this);
254 AttachTrack();
255 }
256
257 // Update channel.
258 if (can_send_track()) {
259 SetSend();
260 AddTrackToStats();
261 } else if (prev_can_send_track) {
262 ClearSend();
263 }
264 attachment_id_ = (track_ ? GenerateUniqueId() : 0);
265 return true;
266}

268void RtpSenderBase::SetSsrc(uint32_t ssrc) {
269 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "RtpSenderBase::SetSsrc");
270 if (stopped_ || ssrc == ssrc_) {
271 return;
272 }
273 // If we are already sending with a particular SSRC, stop sending.
274 if (can_send_track()) {
275 ClearSend();
276 RemoveTrackFromStats();
277 }
278 ssrc_ = ssrc;
279 if (can_send_track()) {
280 SetSend();
281 AddTrackToStats();
282 }
283 if (!init_parameters_.encodings.empty()) {
284 worker_thread_->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&] {
285 RTC_DCHECK(media_channel_);
286 // Get the current parameters, which are constructed from the SDP.
287 // The number of layers in the SDP is currently authoritative to support
288 // SDP munging for Plan-B simulcast with "a=ssrc-group:SIM <ssrc-id>..."
289 // lines as described in RFC 5576.
290 // All fields should be default constructed and the SSRC field set, which
291 // we need to copy.
292 RtpParameters current_parameters =
293 media_channel_->GetRtpSendParameters(ssrc_);
294 RTC_DCHECK_GE(current_parameters.encodings.size(),
295 init_parameters_.encodings.size());
296 for (size_t i = 0; i < init_parameters_.encodings.size(); ++i) {
297 init_parameters_.encodings[i].ssrc =
298 current_parameters.encodings[i].ssrc;
299 init_parameters_.encodings[i].rid = current_parameters.encodings[i].rid;
300 current_parameters.encodings[i] = init_parameters_.encodings[i];
301 }
302 current_parameters.degradation_preference =
303 init_parameters_.degradation_preference;
304 media_channel_->SetRtpSendParameters(ssrc_, current_parameters);
305 init_parameters_.encodings.clear();
306 });
307 }
308 // Attempt to attach the frame decryptor to the current media channel.
309 if (frame_encryptor_) {
310 SetFrameEncryptor(frame_encryptor_);
311 }
312 if (frame_transformer_) {
313 SetEncoderToPacketizerFrameTransformer(frame_transformer_);
314 }
315}
316
317void RtpSenderBase::Stop() {
318 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "RtpSenderBase::Stop");
319 // TODO(deadbeef): Need to do more here to fully stop sending packets.
320 if (stopped_) {
321 return;
322 }
323 if (track_) {
324 DetachTrack();
325 track_->UnregisterObserver(this);
326 }
327 if (can_send_track()) {
328 ClearSend();
329 RemoveTrackFromStats();
330 }
331 media_channel_ = nullptr;
332 set_streams_observer_ = nullptr;
333 stopped_ = true;
334}
335
336RTCError RtpSenderBase::DisableEncodingLayers(
337 const std::vector<std::string>& rids) {
338 if (stopped_) {
339 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_STATE,
340 "Cannot disable encodings on a stopped sender.");
341 }
342
343 if (rids.empty()) {
344 return RTCError::OK();
345 }
346
347 // Check that all the specified layers exist and disable them in the channel.
348 RtpParameters parameters = GetParametersInternal();
349 for (const std::string& rid : rids) {
350 if (absl::c_none_of(parameters.encodings,
351 [&rid](const RtpEncodingParameters& encoding) {
352 return encoding.rid == rid;
353 })) {
354 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
355 "RID: " + rid + " does not refer to a valid layer.");
356 }
357 }
358
359 if (!media_channel_ || !ssrc_) {
360 RemoveEncodingLayers(rids, &init_parameters_.encodings);
361 // Invalidate any transaction upon success.
362 last_transaction_id_.reset();
363 return RTCError::OK();
364 }
365
366 for (RtpEncodingParameters& encoding : parameters.encodings) {
367 // Remain active if not in the disable list.
368 encoding.active &= absl::c_none_of(
369 rids,
370 [&encoding](const std::string& rid) { return encoding.rid == rid; });
371 }
372
373 RTCError result = SetParametersInternal(parameters);
374 if (result.ok()) {
375 disabled_rids_.insert(disabled_rids_.end(), rids.begin(), rids.end());
376 // Invalidate any transaction upon success.
377 last_transaction_id_.reset();
378 }
379 return result;
380}

382void RtpSenderBase::SetEncoderToPacketizerFrameTransformer(
383 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer) {
384 frame_transformer_ = std::move(frame_transformer);
385 if (media_channel_ && ssrc_ && !stopped_) {
386 worker_thread_->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&] {
387 media_channel_->SetEncoderToPacketizerFrameTransformer(
388 ssrc_, frame_transformer_);
389 });
390 }

393LocalAudioSinkAdapter::LocalAudioSinkAdapter() : sink_(nullptr) {}
394
395LocalAudioSinkAdapter::~LocalAudioSinkAdapter() {
396 MutexLock lock(&lock_);
397 if (sink_)
398 sink_->OnClose();
399}
400
401void LocalAudioSinkAdapter::OnData(
402 const void* audio_data,
403 int bits_per_sample,
404 int sample_rate,
405 size_t number_of_channels,
406 size_t number_of_frames,
407 absl::optional<int64_t> absolute_capture_timestamp_ms) {
408 MutexLock lock(&lock_);
409 if (sink_) {
410 sink_->OnData(audio_data, bits_per_sample, sample_rate, number_of_channels,
411 number_of_frames, absolute_capture_timestamp_ms);
412 num_preferred_channels_ = sink_->NumPreferredChannels();
413 }
414}
415
416void LocalAudioSinkAdapter::SetSink(cricket::AudioSource::Sink* sink) {
417 MutexLock lock(&lock_);
418 RTC_DCHECK(!sink || !sink_);
419 sink_ = sink;
420}

448bool AudioRtpSender::CanInsertDtmf() {
449 if (!media_channel_) {
450 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "CanInsertDtmf: No audio channel exists.";
451 return false;
452 }
453 // Check that this RTP sender is active (description has been applied that
454 // matches an SSRC to its ID).
455 if (!ssrc_) {
456 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "CanInsertDtmf: Sender does not have SSRC.";
457 return false;
458 }
459 return worker_thread_->Invoke<bool>(
460 RTC_FROM_HERE, [&] { return voice_media_channel()->CanInsertDtmf(); });
461}
462
463bool AudioRtpSender::InsertDtmf(int code, int duration) {
464 if (!media_channel_) {
465 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "InsertDtmf: No audio channel exists.";
466 return false;
467 }
468 if (!ssrc_) {
469 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "InsertDtmf: Sender does not have SSRC.";
470 return false;
471 }
472 bool success = worker_thread_->Invoke<bool>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&] {
473 return voice_media_channel()->InsertDtmf(ssrc_, code, duration);
474 });
475 if (!success) {
476 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to insert DTMF to channel.";
477 }
478 return success;
479}

485void AudioRtpSender::OnChanged() {
486 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "AudioRtpSender::OnChanged");
487 RTC_DCHECK(!stopped_);
488 if (cached_track_enabled_ != track_->enabled()) {
489 cached_track_enabled_ = track_->enabled();
490 if (can_send_track()) {
491 SetSend();
492 }

505}

523void AudioRtpSender::SetSend() {
524 RTC_DCHECK(!stopped_);
525 RTC_DCHECK(can_send_track());
526 if (!media_channel_) {
527 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "SetAudioSend: No audio channel exists.";
528 return;
529 }
530 cricket::AudioOptions options;
531#if !defined(WEBRTC_CHROMIUM_BUILD) && !defined(WEBRTC_WEBKIT_BUILD)
532 // TODO(tommi): Remove this hack when we move CreateAudioSource out of
533 // PeerConnection. This is a bit of a strange way to apply local audio
534 // options since it is also applied to all streams/channels, local or remote.
535 if (track_->enabled() && audio_track()->GetSource() &&
536 !audio_track()->GetSource()->remote()) {
537 options = audio_track()->GetSource()->options();
538 }
539#endif
540
541 // |track_->enabled()| hops to the signaling thread, so call it before we hop
542 // to the worker thread or else it will deadlock.
543 bool track_enabled = track_->enabled();
544 bool success = worker_thread_->Invoke<bool>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&] {
545 return voice_media_channel()->SetAudioSend(ssrc_, track_enabled, &options,
546 sink_adapter_.get());
547 });
548 if (!success) {
549 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "SetAudioSend: ssrc is incorrect: " << ssrc_;
550 }
551}
552
553void AudioRtpSender::ClearSend() {
554 RTC_DCHECK(ssrc_ != 0);
555 RTC_DCHECK(!stopped_);
556 if (!media_channel_) {
557 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "ClearAudioSend: No audio channel exists.";
558 return;
559 }
560 cricket::AudioOptions options;
561 bool success = worker_thread_->Invoke<bool>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&] {
562 return voice_media_channel()->SetAudioSend(ssrc_, false, &options, nullptr);
563 });
564 if (!success) {
565 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "ClearAudioSend: ssrc is incorrect: " << ssrc_;
566 }
567}

592 SetSend();

607void VideoRtpSender::SetSend() {
608 RTC_DCHECK(!stopped_);
609 RTC_DCHECK(can_send_track());
610 if (!media_channel_) {
611 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "SetVideoSend: No video channel exists.";
612 return;
613 }
614 cricket::VideoOptions options;
615 VideoTrackSourceInterface* source = video_track()->GetSource();
616 if (source) {
617 options.is_screencast = source->is_screencast();
618 options.video_noise_reduction = source->needs_denoising();
619 }
620 options.content_hint = cached_track_content_hint_;
621 switch (cached_track_content_hint_) {
622 case VideoTrackInterface::ContentHint::kNone:
623 break;
624 case VideoTrackInterface::ContentHint::kFluid:
625 options.is_screencast = false;
626 break;
627 case VideoTrackInterface::ContentHint::kDetailed:
628 case VideoTrackInterface::ContentHint::kText:
629 options.is_screencast = true;
630 break;
631 }
632 bool success = worker_thread_->Invoke<bool>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&] {
633 return video_media_channel()->SetVideoSend(ssrc_, &options, video_track());
634 });
635 RTC_DCHECK(success);
636}
637
638void VideoRtpSender::ClearSend() {
639 RTC_DCHECK(ssrc_ != 0);
640 RTC_DCHECK(!stopped_);
641 if (!media_channel_) {
642 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "SetVideoSend: No video channel exists.";
643 return;
644 }
645 // Allow SetVideoSend to fail since |enable| is false and |source| is null.
646 // This the normal case when the underlying media channel has already been
647 // deleted.
648 worker_thread_->Invoke<bool>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&] {
649 return video_media_channel()->SetVideoSend(ssrc_, nullptr, nullptr);
650 });
651}
